                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2625</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-23T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports from various parts of China indicate that the American note has been
                    effective in putting emphatically before the several parties and sections the
                    necessity of national unity, predisposing them to make a compromise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
